    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-19T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-19T06:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_I2"
                        >Italy</persName>)/6–1945: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 559<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KMGNJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-19T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 19, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2673. Gen <persName corresp="#p_MLGWD1">Morgan</persName> has reported from 13
                        Corps<note n="1" xml:id="d559fn1">i. e., from Monfaleone, where <persName
                            corresp="#p_MLGWD1">Morgan</persName>, representing the Supreme Allied
                        Commander, Mediterranean, was quartered while negotiating with Yugoslav
                        military representatives an agreement on the implementation of the Belgrade
                        agreement of June 9.</note> (our 2647, June 16, 11 p.m.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d559fn2">Not printed</note>) that <persName corresp="#p_VMGV1"
                        >Velebit</persName>[,] <persName corresp="#p_JLGAR1">Jovanović</persName>,
                    and Avsić were in Belgrade for consultation and were expected to return noon
                    June 18. Meeting not expected to be resumed until June 19. Maintenance of civil
                    administration system set up since Yugos have been in Venezia Giulia is point
                    which most perturbs them. This system follows Russian model and operates by
                    committees whereas Italian system with modifications as considered advisable by
                        <gloss target="#t_AMG1">AMG</gloss> is system we are determined to use.
                    …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KMGNJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
